&lt;p>&lt;small>Header photo: Space shuttle Discovery landing at Edwards Air Force Base,
California, 9th December, 1992
(&lt;a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/nasacommons/30498961044" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">source: NASA on The Commons&lt;/a>)&lt;/small>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>How to toggle playing/pausing of Spotify using the Pause key in Ubuntu</title><link>https://hugovk.dev/blog/2012/how-to-toggle-playingpausing-of-spotify-using-the-pause-key-in-ubuntu/</link><pubDate>Fri, 13 Jan 2012 13:05:26 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://hugovk.dev/blog/2012/how-to-toggle-playingpausing-of-spotify-using-the-pause-key-in-ubuntu/</guid><description>&lt;p>According to
&lt;a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120509091435/http://www.mabishu.com/blog/2010/11/15/playing-with-d-bus-interface-of-spotify-for-linux/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Mabishu&lt;/a>:&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>After a lot of requests from Linux users, Spotify developers have integrated D-Bus
support in version 0.4.8.282. So, what this means is simply and awesome! Now
Linux developers could use this programmatic interface to interact with Spotify from
other apps.&lt;/p>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In other words, now is quite simple to send «play», «pause», «move next/previous song»
events to Spotify and with this get Spotify fully integrate into our desktop.&lt;/p>&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>To toggle playing and pausing from the terminal, run:&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;code>dbus-send --print-reply --dest=org.mpris.MediaPlayer2.spotify /org/mpris/MediaPlayer2 org.mpris.MediaPlayer2.Player.PlayPause&lt;/code>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>To hook it to the Pause/Break keyboard key:&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Select System -&amp;gt; Preferences -&amp;gt; Keyboard Shortcuts&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Click Add&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Enter any Name: Play or pause Spotify&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Paste in the Command:
&lt;code>dbus-send --print-reply --dest=org.mpris.MediaPlayer2.spotify /org/mpris/MediaPlayer2 org.mpris.MediaPlayer2.Player.PlayPause&lt;/code>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Click Apply&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Click Disabled on the right so it changes to New Shortcut&amp;hellip;&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Press the Pause/Break key&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Click Close&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Listen to music in Spotify and press the Pause/Break key to pause or play the music.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>See the
&lt;a href="http://www.mabishu.com/blog/2010/11/15/playing-with-d-bus-interface-of-spotify-for-linux/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Mabishu&lt;/a>
post to see how to check the other commands you can hook up to other keys.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>(Tested with Ubuntu 10.10 and
&lt;a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120105155314/https://www.spotify.com/fi/download/previews/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Spotify&lt;/a>
for Linux preview 0.6.291)&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>